<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>The Present Perfect with &lt;I&gt;he/she/it&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>For &lt;I&gt;he, she&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;it&lt;/I&gt; form the Present Perfect with &lt;I&gt;has&lt;/I&gt; + past participle. The contracted form of &lt;I&gt;has&lt;/I&gt; is &lt;I&gt;'s&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_10_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;has been &lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;to London twice.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_10_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>She&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'s been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to London twice.</text1a><text2>He &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;has been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; horse riding.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>He&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'s been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; horse riding.</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Form questions, negatives and short answers in the usual way.</sectiontitle2><text3>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Has&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to Paris?</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_10_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>Yes, he &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;has&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text3a><text4>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;hasn't been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to Madrid</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_10_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>She&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'s never been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to Madrid.</text4a></section><section><title>The Present Perfect </title><sectiontitle>The past participle of most verbs is the same as the past tense form.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_10_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>We &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;played&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; football last week.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_10_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Have&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; you ever &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;played&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; football?</text1a><text2>He &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;arrived&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; yesterday.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>He's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;arrived.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>There are a lot of irregular past participles. Some of these are the same as the past tense form.</sectiontitle2><text3>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;bought&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a new car yesterday.</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_10_2_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>We've &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;bought&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a new house.</text3a><text4>They &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;spent&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a lot of money last winter.</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_10_2_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>He's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;spent&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; all his money.</text4a></section><section><title>The Present Perfect </title><sectiontitle>Some past participles are different from the Past tense form.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_10_2_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>I &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;saw&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a film yesterday.</text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_10_2_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>I've &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;seen&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a lot of films.</text1a><text2>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;took&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a photo of our house last week.</text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>Have you &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;taken&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a lot of photos?</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_10_2_16.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>The past participle &lt;I&gt;been&lt;/I&gt; is the past participle of both &lt;I&gt;be&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;go&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle2><text3>It&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'s&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a hot week.</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_10_2_17.mp3</sound3><text3a>It&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;'s been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; a hot week.</text3a><text4>She &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;goes&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to the gym on Tuesdays.</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_10_2_18.mp3</sound4><text4a>She hasn't &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;been&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; to the gym this week.</text4a></section></grammar>